<task id="022" project="ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Meta-tool — FindResources (semantic search over Tool Registry)</title>
    <phase>Phase 2: Tool Registry + Discovery</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>5</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>020, 016</dependencies>
    <blocks>052, 064</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, azure-search, meta-tools</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>BFF code implementation; latency-critical (NFR-01 p95 &lt; 200ms); semantic search wiring; tags include bff-api + ai</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>C</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Group C with 023, 024. All three meta-tools depend on task 020 (data model) but each touches a distinct file under `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/MetaTools/` with no shared service state. Parallelizable per task-create §3.8.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Implement the `FindResources(string userIntent, int topK = 5)` meta-tool — a Semantic Kernel function registered with every Assistant session that performs semantic search over the `spaarke-resource-registry-index` (provisioned in task 016) and returns ranked `ResourceCandidate[]` results respecting the caller's authorization filter. This meta-tool is the discovery primitive used by the Builder Agent and conversational paths when a Tool is not already in the always-on registered set.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET 8 / Azure AI Search engineer with familiarity with `Azure.Search.Documents` SDK, Semantic Kernel `[KernelFunction]` registration patterns, and the existing AI feature module under `Services/Ai/`. Latency-budget aware (NFR-01: p95 &lt; 200ms).
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three concrete outcomes:
    1. **`FindResourcesTool.cs` implementation** — `[KernelFunction]` decorated async method `FindResources(string userIntent, int topK)`. Calls `SearchClient.SearchAsync` against `spaarke-resource-registry-index` with semantic-search configuration; result mapping to `ResourceCandidate[]` (id, displayName, semanticDescription, parameterSchema summary, confidenceScore).
    2. **Authorization filter** — caller's permissions narrow result set before return. A Tool the caller cannot dispatch MUST NOT appear in candidates. Implemented via OData filter on the `requiredPermissions` field of the index, or a post-filter pass if expressible without filter.
    3. **Latency telemetry** — Application Insights custom metric `action_engine.metatool.latency` emitted with `metatool=findResources` dimension; verified in load test (task 064) for NFR-01 p95 &lt; 200ms.

    Deliverable: `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/MetaTools/FindResourcesTool.cs` + tests; SK registration wired in task 025; latency metric wired here.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Spec.md FR-10 + NFR-01 + design.md §7.4.1 worked example all converge: `FindResources("send email to outside counsel about Matter X")` should return ranked candidates including matter-email Tools.

      Existing infrastructure:
      - Task 016 provisioned `spaarke-resource-registry-index` with `semanticDescription` configured as the semantic-search field
      - Task 020 produced `ToolRegistryEntry` (response shape)
      - `Azure.Search.Documents` client is the existing semantic-search SDK already in use elsewhere in BFF (avoid adding new packages)

      Latency budget: `FindResources` p95 &lt; 200ms over the registry index (NFR-01 / G5). Verified by load test in task 064 + App Insights metric. Always-on Tools dispatch budget is &lt; 100ms; this meta-tool is the fallback path for resources NOT in the always-on set.

      Authorization model: caller's permissions narrow the result set. The index entry includes a `requiredPermissions` field; the SearchClient OData filter applies `requiredPermissions/any(p: p eq '&lt;caller-permission&gt;')` semantics. Audit middleware logs the search invocation per ADR-015.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/MetaTools/FindResourcesTool.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/ToolRegistry/ToolRegistryModel.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/AnalysisOrchestrationService.cs</file>
