  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">.NET 8 Minimal API + BackgroundService. Meta-tool runs in-proc within the BFF Chat agent. No Azure Functions.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Endpoint-filter auth applies at the calling endpoint (`/api/chat/`); this meta-tool method receives the authenticated caller via DI / kernel context. Caller authorization is consumed for the result-set filter.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism. `SearchClient` registered once via `AddActionEngineModule()` (singleton keyed by index name). Telemetry client via `[FromServices]`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">PublicContracts boundary. `FindResources` is NOT exposed via the PublicContracts facade — it's an internal SK function. CRUD-side callers MUST NOT inject `IFindResourcesTool` directly.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Audit Tier 2 hash applies to the meta-tool invocation (search query + caller). Tier 3 Cosmos work history written via existing `AuditEnrichmentMiddleware`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Errors returned via ProblemDetails at the calling endpoint; internal exceptions from `SearchClient` wrapped + rethrown with context.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Use existing `Azure.Search.Documents` (already in BFF). No new NuGet packages.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge: placement justification (in BFF — latency-coupled to Chat agent invocation). Publish-size delta from this task = 0 if `Azure.Search.Documents` already transitively present.</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">`FindResources` p95 &lt; 200ms over semantic index. Verified by load test in task 064. This task emits the App Insights metric required for that verification.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">spec.md FR-10: semantic search over `spaarke-resource-registry-index` filtered by caller's authorization. Acceptance: returns `ResourceCandidate[]` with id, descriptions, parameter schema.</constraint>
  </constraints>

