  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm baseline build passes; tasks 020 + 016 merged or branch-loadable; `spaarke-resource-registry-index` provisioned + accessible (verify via `az search` or existing service principal).</step>
    <step order="1">Read all files in `&lt;knowledge&gt;&lt;files&gt;`. Pay close attention to spec.md FR-10 + NFR-01, design.md §7.4.1 worked example, and SprkChatAgent.cs for the existing `[KernelFunction]` pattern.</step>
    <step order="2">Sketch the public signature: `[KernelFunction, Description("Search the Spaarke Tool Registry for resources matching the user's intent. Returns ranked candidates.")]` `Task&lt;ResourceCandidate[]&gt; FindResourcesAsync(string userIntent, int topK = 5)`. Document the response shape `ResourceCandidate` (id, displayName, semanticDescription, parameterSchemaSummary, confidenceScore).</step>
    <step order="3">Implement `FindResourcesTool.cs`. Inject `SearchClient` (keyed by index name `spaarke-resource-registry-index`), `ICallerContext` (or equivalent for caller principal), `TelemetryClient`. Build `SearchOptions` with semantic configuration, `QueryType.Semantic`, `QueryLanguage.EnUs`, `Size = topK`.</step>
    <step order="4">Implement authorization filter. Either (a) build OData filter against `requiredPermissions` collection field with caller's effective permissions, OR (b) execute search + post-filter results. Prefer (a) for latency. Document trade-off in code comments.</step>
    <step order="5">Map `SearchResults&lt;ToolRegistryEntry&gt;` (or the search-projection DTO) into `ResourceCandidate[]`. Trim to top-K. Include semantic-search reranker score in confidenceScore.</step>
    <step order="6">Wire App Insights custom metric `action_engine.metatool.latency` with dimension `metatool=findResources`. Use `Stopwatch` around the `SearchAsync` call; emit on every invocation including failures.</step>
    <step order="7">Write unit tests: (a) happy path returns ranked candidates, (b) empty intent returns empty array (or ProblemDetails-friendly error), (c) topK respected, (d) authorization filter excludes Tools the caller lacks permission for, (e) latency metric emitted. Use `Azure.Search.Documents` SDK in-memory mock or testable interface around `SearchClient`.</step>
    <step order="8">Verify build + tests + format: `dotnet build`, `dotnet test --filter "FindResources"`, `dotnet format`. Manual smoke: run BFF locally with a registered Tool in the dev index and confirm `FindResources("send email")` returns sane candidates.</step>
    <step order="9">Verify NFR-10 (no new packages) + NFR-01 readiness. Local latency smoke under representative load (single-shot via Postman or curl) is not the formal verification — task 064 load-tests p95 over the full index. Confirm metric emission shows in App Insights live metrics during smoke.</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates: `code-review` on `FindResourcesTool.cs`; `adr-check` for ADR-008 (caller auth respected), ADR-010 (DI minimalism), ADR-013 (NOT exposed via PublicContracts), ADR-015 (audit auto-applies via middleware), ADR-019 (errors propagate cleanly to endpoint ProblemDetails), ADR-029 (zero new packages).</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 022 ✅. Update `current-task.md`. Note any latency observations for task 064 awareness.</step>
    <step order="11">Document deviations + latency observations in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/`. Commit with brief recap.</step>
  </steps>

