  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`FindResourcesAsync(string userIntent, int topK = 5)` exists, decorated with `[KernelFunction]` + `[Description]` for SK tool selection.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Returns `ResourceCandidate[]` with id, displayName, semanticDescription, parameterSchemaSummary, confidenceScore — verified by unit test.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Authorization filter applied: Tools the caller cannot dispatch do NOT appear in candidates — verified by unit test with mocked caller principal.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">App Insights custom metric `action_engine.metatool.latency` emitted with `metatool=findResources` dimension on every invocation — verified by unit test on `TelemetryClient` mock.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">FindResources p95 &lt; 200ms over semantic index (verified by load test in task 064 — NFR-01). This task wires the latency metric; the load test gates the SLO.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No new NuGet packages added (NFR-10 preserved). `Azure.Search.Documents` already transitively present.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">NOT exposed via `PublicContracts/IActionEngineFacade.cs` — verified by grep (ADR-013 boundary).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Supports spec gate G2 (conversational invocation resolves intent → Tool) and G5 (FindResources p95 SLO).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Authorization filter implementation choice (OData vs post-filter) directly affects p95 latency. OData filter pushes work to the Search service; post-filter pulls more rows then filters in-proc. Default to OData; fall back to post-filter only if the index schema makes OData filtering impractical.

    The `requiredPermissions` index field is established by task 016 (index provisioning) + task 020 (model) + the indexer pipeline. If this task discovers the field shape is awkward for OData filtering, escalate to coordinate a schema adjustment in 016 — DO NOT silently shift logic to post-filter.

    Task 064 (load test) will validate p95 with realistic index size. This task should aim for &lt;100ms p95 locally under light load to leave headroom for production scaling.
  </notes>

